1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
[English subtitles are available]

2
00:01:36,350 --> 00:01:42,229
[I Don't Want to Be Friends With You]

3
00:01:44,580 --> 00:01:45,770
Do you want to go or not?

4
00:01:45,860 --> 00:01:46,840
No!

5
00:01:47,300 --> 00:01:48,880
Fine! I'll just go by myself.

6
00:01:49,890 --> 00:01:50,990
I'm leaving.

7
00:01:56,900 --> 00:01:59,280
Li Jin Bu! Are you going
to cooperate or not?

8
00:02:00,060 --> 00:02:01,280
I'm counting.

9
00:02:01,890 --> 00:02:02,770
One.

10
00:02:04,340 --> 00:02:06,190
Two.

11
00:02:10,810 --> 00:02:11,960
Oh, come on!

12
00:02:12,660 --> 00:02:15,290
Where the hell do you want to go?

13
00:02:15,380 --> 00:02:17,370
I want to see the aurora.

14
00:02:17,460 --> 00:02:18,840
It's May now, middle of summer.

15
00:02:18,930 --> 00:02:20,250
There's no aurora.

16
00:02:20,340 --> 00:02:21,210
Yes there is! On TV.

17
00:02:21,300 --> 00:02:22,530
Well, why don't you go watch TV

18
00:02:22,620 --> 00:02:23,920
and we can cancel our vacation?

19
00:02:24,579 --> 00:02:25,290
You just keep standing here,

20
00:02:25,380 --> 00:02:25,810
don't move.

21
00:02:25,900 --> 00:02:28,300
Let's see whether there's
any polar bear or penguin.

22
00:02:28,390 --> 00:02:29,210
Ok?

23
00:02:29,290 --> 00:02:30,970
It's like you know everything.

24
00:02:31,050 --> 00:02:32,770
We are not going anywhere today.

25
00:02:32,860 --> 00:02:34,720
Let's just stay at home, alright?

26
00:02:38,820 --> 00:02:39,880
Don't move!

27
00:02:41,730 --> 00:02:42,890
I just know!

28
00:02:42,980 --> 00:02:45,030
I will see the aurora!

29
00:02:50,940 --> 00:02:53,590
[Episode 9: Later I Realised That There
Really Was an Aurora That Year]

30
00:03:12,380 --> 00:03:13,800
You're leaving?

31
00:03:15,100 --> 00:03:16,760
Are you still coming tomorrow?

32
00:03:17,050 --> 00:03:18,400
I'll still be here tomorrow.

33
00:03:19,620 --> 00:03:21,280
If you want me to help
you study in the future,

34
00:03:21,820 --> 00:03:23,310
you have to do something first.

35
00:03:23,680 --> 00:03:24,829
What?

36
00:03:26,930 --> 00:03:28,880
There are 75 pages in this notebook,

37
00:03:29,370 --> 00:03:31,130
and all subjects are covered.

38
00:03:31,220 --> 00:03:32,670
If you can memorize it all,

39
00:03:32,980 --> 00:03:35,040
I'll be helping you until the NEMT.

40
00:03:35,970 --> 00:03:37,490
75 pages.

41
00:03:37,579 --> 00:03:39,880
That's too much!

42
00:03:40,100 --> 00:03:41,570
So forget it.

43
00:03:42,540 --> 00:03:43,370
No!

44
00:03:43,450 --> 00:03:44,680
I'll memorize it all.

45
00:04:12,250 --> 00:04:16,079
[Tieyuan No. 3 Middle School]

46
00:04:21,660 --> 00:04:23,100
[Tieyuan No. 3 Middle School]

47
00:04:23,100 --> 00:04:25,650
Morning, Dean.

48
00:04:25,650 --> 00:04:27,160
[Tieyuan No. 3 Middle School]

49
00:04:42,180 --> 00:04:43,010
Feeling tired?

50
00:04:43,090 --> 00:04:44,830
I can't feel my arms.

51
00:04:44,980 --> 00:04:46,409
I've been saying that, I can handle this.

52
00:04:46,490 --> 00:04:46,940
You can take a rest.

53
00:04:47,030 --> 00:04:47,290
I got this.

54
00:04:47,370 --> 00:04:48,409
It's ok.

55
00:04:48,500 --> 00:04:49,360
Let go.

56
00:04:49,450 --> 00:04:50,680
Wipe your sweat,

57
00:04:50,770 --> 00:04:52,840
otherwise you'll catch cold.

58
00:05:01,330 --> 00:05:02,090
Are you thirsty?

59
00:05:02,180 --> 00:05:03,520
I'll get you some water.

60
00:05:05,530 --> 00:05:07,050
What are you doing on May Day Holiday?

61
00:05:07,140 --> 00:05:08,710
Do you want to hang out with me?

62
00:05:08,810 --> 00:05:10,000
Out?

63
00:05:10,460 --> 00:05:11,330
Out where?

64
00:05:11,420 --> 00:05:12,300
Mohe county.

65
00:05:12,450 --> 00:05:13,890
The northmost county in China?

66
00:05:13,980 --> 00:05:14,490
Right.

67
00:05:14,580 --> 00:05:15,840
The northmost part of China.

68
00:05:16,180 --> 00:05:17,060
Do you want to go?

69
00:05:17,530 --> 00:05:18,370
No. I won't go.

70
00:05:18,460 --> 00:05:19,640
It's too cold.

71
00:05:19,730 --> 00:05:20,880
Although it's cold,

72
00:05:21,020 --> 00:05:22,960
you can see aurora there.

73
00:05:25,260 --> 00:05:26,350
Aurora?

74
00:05:26,430 --> 00:05:27,090
Right.

75
00:05:27,180 --> 00:05:28,120
Aurora.

76
00:05:29,340 --> 00:05:31,240
It's the only place in
China can you see aurora.

77
00:05:32,580 --> 00:05:34,170
Suddenly change your mind?

78
00:05:34,250 --> 00:05:35,490
Is it real?

79
00:05:35,570 --> 00:05:36,630
Don't you lie to me.

80
00:05:36,720 --> 00:05:38,070
Have I ever lied to you?

81
00:05:39,180 --> 00:05:39,730
Ok.

82
00:05:39,820 --> 00:05:40,950
I'll go with you.

83
00:05:41,040 --> 00:05:42,280
I've always wanted to see the aurora.

84
00:05:42,370 --> 00:05:43,570
But my mum won't take.

85
00:05:43,659 --> 00:05:44,480
Trust me,

86
00:05:44,570 --> 00:05:45,490
I'll take you there.

87
00:05:45,570 --> 00:05:46,840
And I'll make sure you see the aurora.

88
00:05:48,770 --> 00:05:51,040
Why do you put the dry one back?

89
00:05:53,980 --> 00:05:55,200
I'll do it again.

90
00:06:11,970 --> 00:06:12,920
Does it hurt?

91
00:06:54,380 --> 00:06:55,510
Why are you smiling?

92
00:06:55,600 --> 00:06:56,840
Hang the sheets up.

93
00:07:22,940 --> 00:07:24,720
I've never seen the aurora.

94
00:07:24,810 --> 00:07:26,450
I want to come along too.

95
00:07:26,540 --> 00:07:27,050
Yeah.

96
00:07:27,130 --> 00:07:28,110
Come with us.

97
00:07:28,540 --> 00:07:29,410
I can't.

98
00:07:29,500 --> 00:07:30,440
I need to resist all temptation,

99
00:07:30,530 --> 00:07:31,800
and focus on the notebook.

100
00:07:32,020 --> 00:07:34,650
Are you really going to memorize
the whole notebook?

101
00:07:34,730 --> 00:07:35,370
Of course!

102
00:07:35,460 --> 00:07:36,640
A deal's a deal.

103
00:07:37,690 --> 00:07:38,210
Right.

104
00:07:38,300 --> 00:07:39,320
I believe in you.

105
00:07:46,980 --> 00:07:47,860
Hua,

106
00:07:48,100 --> 00:07:49,890
if you do see the aurora,

107
00:07:49,980 --> 00:07:51,409
could you make a wish for me?

108
00:07:51,500 --> 00:07:52,670
About what?

109
00:07:55,220 --> 00:07:56,510
I wish

110
00:07:56,700 --> 00:07:59,520
my parents can live
a long and healthy life,

111
00:08:00,300 --> 00:08:01,850
and we can live a long
and healthy life too,

112
00:08:01,940 --> 00:08:02,890
and we'll be together forever.

113
00:08:02,980 --> 00:08:03,970
We won't be parted.

114
00:08:04,060 --> 00:08:04,940
Trust me.

115
00:08:20,460 --> 00:08:21,210
What're you doing?

116
00:08:21,300 --> 00:08:22,470
Are you going to break the house down?

117
00:08:24,260 --> 00:08:24,770
Mum,

118
00:08:24,860 --> 00:08:26,210
that cotton overcoat my dad bought for me,

119
00:08:26,300 --> 00:08:27,010
the very thick one

120
00:08:27,090 --> 00:08:27,650
with fur collar,

121
00:08:27,740 --> 00:08:28,790
where is it?

122
00:08:28,880 --> 00:08:29,850
You didn't want to wear it,

123
00:08:29,940 --> 00:08:31,010
so I put it away.

124
00:08:31,100 --> 00:08:31,890
Why?

125
00:08:31,980 --> 00:08:33,030
You want to wear it?

126
00:08:33,440 --> 00:08:34,289
Yes.

127
00:08:34,370 --> 00:08:35,230
Help me find it out.

128
00:08:35,320 --> 00:08:36,409
And that pair of shoes,

129
00:08:36,500 --> 00:08:37,210
the thick pair

130
00:08:37,299 --> 00:08:38,049
with fur inside.

131
00:08:38,140 --> 00:08:39,480
Help me find that too.

132
00:08:39,740 --> 00:08:40,450
Look,

133
00:08:40,530 --> 00:08:42,049
you have feet of size 44,

134
00:08:42,140 --> 00:08:43,799
What do you want to do with my shoes?

135
00:08:44,100 --> 00:08:44,890
Never mind.

136
00:08:44,980 --> 00:08:45,530
I need it.

137
00:08:45,620 --> 00:08:46,770
The hot water bag,

138
00:08:46,860 --> 00:08:47,490
and thermos.

139
00:08:47,570 --> 00:08:48,990
I need them all.

140
00:08:50,850 --> 00:08:52,190
thermos?

141
00:08:53,980 --> 00:08:55,590
When did you become such a baby?

142
00:08:57,250 --> 00:08:57,970
Hua,

143
00:08:58,060 --> 00:08:58,890
look.

144
00:08:58,980 --> 00:09:00,750
I never wore this dress,

145
00:09:00,970 --> 00:09:02,330
not even once.

146
00:09:02,410 --> 00:09:03,330
You should wear it to see the aurora.

147
00:09:03,410 --> 00:09:04,290
No.

148
00:09:04,380 --> 00:09:06,560
It's so inconvenient.

149
00:09:06,860 --> 00:09:08,600
But it's so pretty.

150
00:09:09,540 --> 00:09:10,420
Hua,

151
00:09:10,660 --> 00:09:12,280
look what I got you.

152
00:09:13,410 --> 00:09:14,610
Listen to me,

153
00:09:14,700 --> 00:09:16,010
once you wear this hat,

154
00:09:16,100 --> 00:09:16,930
your whole body

155
00:09:17,020 --> 00:09:18,400
will be so warm.

156
00:09:20,130 --> 00:09:20,970
Back in the days,

157
00:09:21,060 --> 00:09:22,930
when I worked on the farm
at minus 20 Celsius,

158
00:09:23,020 --> 00:09:24,450
this is what kept me warm.

159
00:09:24,530 --> 00:09:25,720
Come on, try it.

160
00:09:26,140 --> 00:09:27,480
It's so cool.

161
00:09:28,100 --> 00:09:28,980
Looks good.

162
00:09:29,490 --> 00:09:30,370
Forget it!

163
00:09:30,460 --> 00:09:31,490
It's the middle of summer.

164
00:09:31,570 --> 00:09:33,080
This hat is too thick.

165
00:09:33,420 --> 00:09:36,200
You know nothing.

166
00:09:36,290 --> 00:09:37,290
Mohe county is much colder

167
00:09:37,380 --> 00:09:38,490
than where we are,

168
00:09:38,580 --> 00:09:40,080
it's snowing there.

169
00:09:40,900 --> 00:09:42,000
Right,

170
00:09:42,440 --> 00:09:43,090
well,

171
00:09:43,180 --> 00:09:43,490
Hua,

172
00:09:43,570 --> 00:09:44,450
one more thing.

173
00:09:44,540 --> 00:09:46,450
Here's 100 RMB from your auntie.

174
00:09:46,530 --> 00:09:47,230
Since you're away from home,

175
00:09:47,310 --> 00:09:48,490
you need to keep some spare money.

176
00:09:48,580 --> 00:09:48,890
Take it.

177
00:09:48,970 --> 00:09:50,090
It's alright, uncle.

178
00:09:50,170 --> 00:09:51,690
I still have a lot of New Year money left.

179
00:09:51,780 --> 00:09:52,930
Besides, I've already bought the ticket,

180
00:09:53,020 --> 00:09:54,130
so I don't need to spend a dime.

181
00:09:54,220 --> 00:09:55,670
Nonsense.

182
00:09:55,820 --> 00:09:56,650
All those friends of yours,

183
00:09:56,740 --> 00:09:58,850
the food and drinks, it all cost money.

184
00:09:58,940 --> 00:10:00,520
Besides, you should give them a treat.

185
00:10:00,610 --> 00:10:01,350
Take it.

186
00:10:01,440 --> 00:10:02,490
Your aunt will be mad if you don't.

187
00:10:02,580 --> 00:10:03,470
And I will be mad too.

188
00:10:03,810 --> 00:10:04,330
Take it.

189
00:10:04,420 --> 00:10:04,850
Come on.

190
00:10:04,940 --> 00:10:06,280
Thanks, uncle.

191
00:10:07,100 --> 00:10:07,560
Right.

192
00:10:07,650 --> 00:10:08,350
You girls go on.

193
00:10:08,430 --> 00:10:09,680
Call me if you need anything.

194
00:10:15,690 --> 00:10:16,910
Hua,

195
00:10:19,300 --> 00:10:20,180
here,

196
00:10:20,300 --> 00:10:22,510
there's 100 RMB I saved.

197
00:10:22,940 --> 00:10:23,880
Take it.

198
00:10:25,100 --> 00:10:26,280
How about you?

199
00:10:26,420 --> 00:10:27,010
I'm fine.

200
00:10:27,100 --> 00:10:28,400
I don't need it anyway.

201
00:10:29,980 --> 00:10:31,430
But if there's money left,

202
00:10:31,620 --> 00:10:33,190
give it back.

203
00:10:38,900 --> 00:10:40,790
[Peony Hotel]

204
00:10:50,570 --> 00:10:51,760
What's this about?

205
00:10:52,500 --> 00:10:54,290
Mohe county is the coldest place in China.

206
00:10:54,380 --> 00:10:55,170
Hua's not good with cold,

207
00:10:55,260 --> 00:10:56,330
the more clothes, the better.

208
00:10:56,410 --> 00:10:57,970
It is May,

209
00:10:58,050 --> 00:10:58,970
it can't be that cold.

210
00:10:59,050 --> 00:11:00,350
It will be that cold.

211
00:11:00,660 --> 00:11:02,130
The temperature will
drop below zero at night.

212
00:11:02,220 --> 00:11:03,010
You've never been there,

213
00:11:03,100 --> 00:11:03,980
so you don't know.

214
00:11:05,940 --> 00:11:07,510
Xiao, I'm warning you,

215
00:11:07,700 --> 00:11:08,930
I trusted Hua with you.

216
00:11:09,020 --> 00:11:10,130
Take good care of her.

217
00:11:10,220 --> 00:11:11,200
Trust me.

218
00:11:11,370 --> 00:11:12,480
I'm where she is.

219
00:11:12,570 --> 00:11:13,760
She'll be safe with me.

220
00:11:16,090 --> 00:11:18,600
Do I really need to wear it now?

221
00:11:18,780 --> 00:11:19,880
Of course.

222
00:11:20,050 --> 00:11:21,590
It'll get colder as we go north.

223
00:11:34,620 --> 00:11:36,320
Mind your legs.

224
00:11:36,700 --> 00:11:39,490
Snacks and beverages.

225
00:11:39,580 --> 00:11:40,810
Anyone want snacks and beverages?

226
00:11:40,900 --> 00:11:42,510
Here, mind your legs.

227
00:11:42,980 --> 00:11:45,060
Snacks and beverages.

228
00:11:45,140 --> 00:11:46,570
Anyone want snacks and beverages?

229
00:11:46,660 --> 00:11:47,410
Excuse me.

230
00:11:47,500 --> 00:11:48,600
You want something to eat?

231
00:11:51,970 --> 00:11:53,270
I want some ham sausages.

232
00:11:53,660 --> 00:11:54,590
Two sausages please.

233
00:11:55,490 --> 00:11:57,670
Here you go.

234
00:11:57,900 --> 00:11:58,960
Two yuan.

235
00:12:06,170 --> 00:12:08,040
Snacks and beverages?

236
00:12:08,130 --> 00:12:09,690
Anyone want snacks and beverages?

237
00:12:09,780 --> 00:12:11,310
Mind your legs please.

238
00:12:18,220 --> 00:12:19,400
Take a snap later.

239
00:12:19,620 --> 00:12:20,990
We'll be there when you wake up.

240
00:12:46,940 --> 00:12:49,240
I've slept enough,

241
00:12:49,410 --> 00:12:51,360
when will we be there?

242
00:12:51,780 --> 00:12:52,490
Wait here,

243
00:12:52,580 --> 00:12:53,790
I'll go check.

244
00:13:04,090 --> 00:13:07,070
[Welcome to Hengdaohezi]

245
00:13:17,180 --> 00:13:18,320
So?

246
00:13:19,500 --> 00:13:20,720
We're stuck here,

247
00:13:20,860 --> 00:13:22,070
it's snowing heavily,

248
00:13:22,260 --> 00:13:24,130
and the railway ahead broke down.

249
00:13:24,220 --> 00:13:25,710
Repairs are underway.

250
00:13:26,020 --> 00:13:27,590
So how long will it take?

251
00:13:27,940 --> 00:13:29,410
Maybe one day,

252
00:13:29,500 --> 00:13:31,080
or maybe a few days.

253
00:13:32,340 --> 00:13:33,850
So what should we do?

254
00:13:33,940 --> 00:13:35,710
We have to spend the night here.

255
00:13:35,900 --> 00:13:37,710
I just phoned my dad,

256
00:13:37,810 --> 00:13:40,040
and he told us to go back tomorrow.

257
00:13:46,580 --> 00:13:48,910
I haven't seen him for three years.

258
00:13:49,540 --> 00:13:51,910
He was supposed to be home last year,

259
00:13:52,130 --> 00:13:53,530
but there was an
emergency mission for him.

260
00:13:53,620 --> 00:13:54,870
So he didn't come back.

261
00:13:55,210 --> 00:13:58,200
Last time I saw him, I was a little boy,

262
00:13:58,610 --> 00:14:00,520
and now I've grown up.

263
00:14:04,100 --> 00:14:05,240
That's alright.

264
00:14:05,820 --> 00:14:07,970
Perhaps the railway
will be ready tomorrow.

265
00:14:08,060 --> 00:14:09,050
We just need to wait.

266
00:14:09,140 --> 00:14:10,720
After all, we've come all the way here.

267
00:14:10,810 --> 00:14:12,080
It's only one night.

268
00:14:12,620 --> 00:14:14,110
It's too cold here.

269
00:14:14,330 --> 00:14:16,170
We won't be cold with
all those clothes on.

270
00:14:16,260 --> 00:14:17,430
I'll wait with you.

271
00:14:19,780 --> 00:14:20,690
Ok.

272
00:14:20,780 --> 00:14:21,650
Let's go eat first,

273
00:14:21,740 --> 00:14:22,620
fuel up.

274
00:14:22,700 --> 00:14:23,890
What should we eat?

275
00:14:23,980 --> 00:14:26,080
The standard railway station meal.

276
00:14:36,820 --> 00:14:39,680
That's it?

277
00:14:40,700 --> 00:14:42,080
You don't like it?

278
00:14:42,170 --> 00:14:43,250
I'll get you something else.

279
00:14:43,340 --> 00:14:44,210
That's ok.

280
00:14:44,300 --> 00:14:44,970
This is fine.

281
00:14:45,050 --> 00:14:46,320
It's alright.

282
00:14:53,540 --> 00:14:55,270
Are you not comfortable with this?

283
00:14:56,860 --> 00:14:57,840
What?

284
00:14:58,340 --> 00:14:59,440
Nothing.

285
00:14:59,780 --> 00:15:00,410
Too hot?

286
00:15:00,500 --> 00:15:01,640
Let me blow it.

287
00:15:11,220 --> 00:15:12,720
To be honest,

288
00:15:13,940 --> 00:15:15,850
I'm not quite comfortable with this.

289
00:15:15,940 --> 00:15:17,010
With what?

290
00:15:17,100 --> 00:15:18,450
Is it too cold here?

291
00:15:18,540 --> 00:15:19,680
No.

292
00:15:20,060 --> 00:15:21,440
It's not that.

293
00:15:21,660 --> 00:15:22,990
I mean,

294
00:15:23,580 --> 00:15:26,720
with someone being so careful to me.

295
00:15:28,460 --> 00:15:31,040
I'm used to being alone,

296
00:15:31,130 --> 00:15:33,160
and solving everything by myself.

297
00:15:33,540 --> 00:15:34,490
For all those years,

298
00:15:34,580 --> 00:15:36,650
you're the first one
who's been so kind to me.

299
00:15:36,740 --> 00:15:38,130
You get everything ready for me,

300
00:15:38,220 --> 00:15:40,120
care so much for me.

301
00:15:40,580 --> 00:15:41,700
So,

302
00:15:42,740 --> 00:15:44,350
I'm not quite comfortable with this.

303
00:15:45,220 --> 00:15:46,530
Well, you should stay
with me in the future,

304
00:15:46,620 --> 00:15:47,800
then you'll get used to it.

305
00:15:49,560 --> 00:15:50,440
Here.

306
00:15:53,250 --> 00:15:55,440
So, why do your parents leave you alone?

307
00:15:56,820 --> 00:15:57,960
My mum,

308
00:15:58,460 --> 00:16:00,280
she can't even take care of herself.

309
00:16:10,230 --> 00:16:17,830
[Welcome to Hengdaohezi]

310
00:16:41,330 --> 00:16:42,310
Sleep well?

311
00:16:42,740 --> 00:16:43,720
Have some hot water.

312
00:16:47,170 --> 00:16:48,490
Did the snow stop?

313
00:16:48,580 --> 00:16:49,410
Yes.

314
00:16:49,490 --> 00:16:51,030
The snow is very deep.

315
00:16:51,780 --> 00:16:53,160
Do you want to go outside and see?

316
00:16:54,330 --> 00:16:55,240
Let's go.

317
00:16:57,940 --> 00:16:59,120
Duan Xiao.

318
00:17:11,300 --> 00:17:12,349
Dad!

319
00:17:13,569 --> 00:17:14,880
Don't embarrass me.

320
00:17:15,060 --> 00:17:15,810
I've come all the way here,

321
00:17:15,890 --> 00:17:16,780
on a snowy night.

322
00:17:16,869 --> 00:17:19,040
And I'm not here to watch you cry.

323
00:17:21,609 --> 00:17:22,910
My son.

324
00:17:29,060 --> 00:17:30,480
You're much taller,

325
00:17:31,100 --> 00:17:32,320
and thinner.

326
00:17:35,940 --> 00:17:36,970
You must be

327
00:17:37,060 --> 00:17:38,400
Li Jin Bu.

328
00:17:38,820 --> 00:17:39,840
Nice to meet you, uncle.

329
00:17:40,500 --> 00:17:41,840
Sit down.

330
00:17:45,050 --> 00:17:46,270
How's your mum?

331
00:17:46,420 --> 00:17:47,090
Don't worry.

332
00:17:47,180 --> 00:17:48,440
Everything's great.

333
00:17:50,450 --> 00:17:51,680
Great.

334
00:17:55,260 --> 00:17:57,910
Here's the sweater and
trousers she knitted for you.

335
00:17:58,740 --> 00:18:00,170
It's so thick.

336
00:18:00,260 --> 00:18:02,410
And here's the medicinal
liquor my aunt made.

337
00:18:02,500 --> 00:18:03,600
Great!

338
00:18:03,700 --> 00:18:04,450
And this,

339
00:18:04,530 --> 00:18:05,370
beef.

340
00:18:05,460 --> 00:18:06,840
Eat up with your comrades.

341
00:18:06,930 --> 00:18:08,270
Great, I love this.

342
00:18:08,490 --> 00:18:09,250
And this,

343
00:18:09,340 --> 00:18:10,730
tea from my grandma.

344
00:18:10,820 --> 00:18:11,870
Dahongpao tea.

345
00:18:15,260 --> 00:18:16,030
Uncle,

346
00:18:16,120 --> 00:18:17,360
have some water.

347
00:18:19,050 --> 00:18:20,290
How's the northeast?

348
00:18:20,370 --> 00:18:21,290
It's great,

349
00:18:21,370 --> 00:18:22,530
but too cold.

350
00:18:22,620 --> 00:18:24,690
It's the first time I see snow in May.

351
00:18:24,770 --> 00:18:26,010
Yeah, it's just like that.

352
00:18:26,090 --> 00:18:27,000
Very cold here.

353
00:18:27,660 --> 00:18:29,490
Duan Xian has been very strong,

354
00:18:29,580 --> 00:18:30,880
he can stand the cold.

355
00:18:31,120 --> 00:18:32,920
You come a long way with him,

356
00:18:33,010 --> 00:18:34,130
and it wasn't easy for you.

357
00:18:34,220 --> 00:18:35,200
That's ok.

358
00:18:35,300 --> 00:18:37,120
Duan Xiao has told me a lot about you.

359
00:18:37,820 --> 00:18:38,790
What about me?

360
00:18:38,880 --> 00:18:40,400
That you're very handsome,

361
00:18:40,490 --> 00:18:41,690
and you can drive a tank,

362
00:18:41,780 --> 00:18:43,560
and that you've let him touch the cannon.

363
00:18:44,060 --> 00:18:45,730
However, once I met you,

364
00:18:45,820 --> 00:18:47,430
I think you are more
handsome than he said.

365
00:18:48,410 --> 00:18:49,480
So,

366
00:18:49,620 --> 00:18:51,770
I didn't embarrass him, right?

367
00:18:51,860 --> 00:18:53,490
Dad, tell her about the army.

368
00:18:53,580 --> 00:18:54,370
She's never seen it.

369
00:18:54,460 --> 00:18:55,560
In the army...

370
00:18:55,880 --> 00:18:56,930
In the army,

371
00:18:57,010 --> 00:18:58,030
there's plenty of discipline

372
00:18:58,110 --> 00:19:00,010
but it's also very fun.

373
00:19:00,090 --> 00:19:01,090
There are

374
00:19:01,180 --> 00:19:02,570
many cannons in the army.

375
00:19:02,660 --> 00:19:03,490
And you know what,

376
00:19:03,580 --> 00:19:04,690
there are many guns too.

377
00:19:04,780 --> 00:19:07,090
It's very interesting.

378
00:19:07,180 --> 00:19:10,290
I can see all kinds of
guns and cannons there,

379
00:19:10,380 --> 00:19:11,730
bullets too.

380
00:19:11,820 --> 00:19:12,850
So much fun.

381
00:19:12,940 --> 00:19:14,650
And this time,

382
00:19:14,730 --> 00:19:15,690
I got to see some large tanks.

383
00:19:15,780 --> 00:19:17,080
Very large.

384
00:19:25,490 --> 00:19:28,690
[Departure]

385
00:19:28,690 --> 00:19:29,330
I've got missions,

386
00:19:29,420 --> 00:19:30,400
so I can't stay for long.

387
00:19:30,620 --> 00:19:31,960
You should go back.

388
00:19:32,770 --> 00:19:34,630
I am so glad to see you.

389
00:19:34,780 --> 00:19:36,760
Especially you, comrade Li Jin Bu.

390
00:19:37,050 --> 00:19:37,840
So nice

391
00:19:37,930 --> 00:19:39,150
to meet you.

392
00:19:40,520 --> 00:19:41,420
Son,

393
00:19:41,740 --> 00:19:42,990
remember our slogan?

394
00:19:43,080 --> 00:19:44,040
Of course.

395
00:19:44,820 --> 00:19:45,890
Comrade Duan Xiao.

396
00:19:45,970 --> 00:19:46,850
Here.

397
00:19:47,100 --> 00:19:48,440
My mission is

398
00:19:48,730 --> 00:19:49,530
fighting till the end

399
00:19:49,610 --> 00:19:50,430
and protecting our country.

400
00:19:50,520 --> 00:19:51,510
My mission is

401
00:19:51,590 --> 00:19:52,580
studying hard and

402
00:19:52,670 --> 00:19:53,530
taking care of Mum.

403
00:19:53,620 --> 00:19:54,490
Let's fight together

404
00:19:54,580 --> 00:19:55,870
and never give up.

405
00:20:04,080 --> 00:20:05,210
I'm leaving.

406
00:20:08,620 --> 00:20:10,070
Goodbye, uncle.

407
00:20:25,180 --> 00:20:26,400
Are there really auroras

408
00:20:26,780 --> 00:20:28,110
in May?

409
00:20:30,260 --> 00:20:31,800
Maybe

410
00:20:33,320 --> 00:20:34,540
there is.

411
00:20:35,050 --> 00:20:36,220
You lied!

412
00:20:36,540 --> 00:20:37,790
There's no aurora.

413
00:20:39,330 --> 00:20:40,920
I wanted to make wishes.

414
00:20:41,460 --> 00:20:42,950
I'll be your aurora,

415
00:20:43,610 --> 00:20:45,270
and realize all your wishes.

416
00:20:48,450 --> 00:20:50,970
This is the first time
I take the green train,

417
00:20:51,060 --> 00:20:53,950
the first time I see snow in May,

418
00:20:54,290 --> 00:20:55,850
and the first time I realize that

419
00:20:55,940 --> 00:20:57,790
even without a father's presence,

420
00:20:57,880 --> 00:20:59,690
the family can still be warm.

421
00:21:00,300 --> 00:21:01,700
What a pity!

422
00:21:01,860 --> 00:21:04,010
We didn't get to see the aurora.

423
00:21:04,090 --> 00:21:06,270
But until many years later did I know,

424
00:21:06,500 --> 00:21:08,120
that year, in May.

425
00:21:08,260 --> 00:21:08,530
Here.

426
00:21:08,610 --> 00:21:10,400
There really was aurora.

427
00:21:18,490 --> 00:21:20,850
Duan Xiao's father is
very tall and handsome.

428
00:21:20,930 --> 00:21:22,170
He's so cool.

429
00:21:22,250 --> 00:21:23,970
I want a dad like that.

430
00:21:24,060 --> 00:21:27,160
My dad was also very
handsome when he's young,

431
00:21:27,620 --> 00:21:29,920
and my mum was the
prettiest girl in the factory.

432
00:21:31,810 --> 00:21:34,550
Why didn't I get their good looks?

433
00:21:35,980 --> 00:21:37,630
I didn't either.

434
00:21:39,970 --> 00:21:42,120
You told me that I look like your mum.

435
00:21:42,700 --> 00:21:44,690
Almost the same, ok?

436
00:21:44,780 --> 00:21:46,490
Then you sure didn't get her good looks.

437
00:21:46,570 --> 00:21:47,410
Look at yourself,

438
00:21:47,500 --> 00:21:49,120
you look so ordinary.

439
00:21:51,060 --> 00:21:52,090
I'm better than my mum

440
00:21:52,170 --> 00:21:54,330
in every single way, ok?

441
00:21:54,420 --> 00:21:55,030
Look at us,

442
00:21:55,120 --> 00:21:57,320
do we have anything alike?

443
00:21:57,860 --> 00:21:59,570
What's the point of comparing us?

444
00:21:59,650 --> 00:22:01,120
I'm not your mother.

445
00:22:01,530 --> 00:22:02,630
It seems that

446
00:22:03,610 --> 00:22:05,590
your dad is pretty tall.

447
00:22:06,060 --> 00:22:06,920
None of your business.

448
00:22:07,010 --> 00:22:08,320
Keep memorizing your notebook.

449
00:22:13,220 --> 00:22:13,970
I think I'm dying

450
00:22:14,060 --> 00:22:18,520
on this notebook.

451
00:22:21,580 --> 00:22:23,750
Before the class is dismissed,

452
00:22:25,410 --> 00:22:27,250
I want to announce that
on September 15th, 2000,

453
00:22:27,340 --> 00:22:29,610
the 27th Summer Olympic Games

454
00:22:29,690 --> 00:22:31,920
will be held at Sydney, Australia.

455
00:22:32,060 --> 00:22:33,730
To uphold the Olympic spirits...

456
00:22:33,820 --> 00:22:34,970
This is pointless.

457
00:22:35,060 --> 00:22:36,930
On June 1st, we will have
a school sports meeting.

458
00:22:37,020 --> 00:22:37,930
Each of you,

459
00:22:38,020 --> 00:22:39,410
shall participate in at least one race.

460
00:22:39,490 --> 00:22:40,040
Mao Ying Jian.

461
00:22:40,130 --> 00:22:40,530
Here.

462
00:22:40,620 --> 00:22:41,360
Take the form.

463
00:22:41,450 --> 00:22:42,330
You're in charge of taking records.

464
00:22:42,540 --> 00:22:43,890
And again,

465
00:22:43,980 --> 00:22:44,880
each of you

466
00:22:44,970 --> 00:22:45,930
must participate in the race.

467
00:22:46,020 --> 00:22:47,240
Don't chicken out.

468
00:22:48,020 --> 00:22:49,120
Teacher.

469
00:22:49,700 --> 00:22:52,030
I've got hardly a
speck of athletic ability,

470
00:22:52,120 --> 00:22:53,350
what race can I take part in?

471
00:22:53,690 --> 00:22:55,030
You can choose field
events instead of races.

472
00:22:55,110 --> 00:22:57,280
Discus throw or shot push or both.

473
00:22:57,700 --> 00:22:59,070
I don't want to choose either of them.

474
00:22:59,780 --> 00:23:00,610
Teacher.

475
00:23:00,700 --> 00:23:01,850
For the honour of our class,

476
00:23:01,930 --> 00:23:03,250
I'm going to sign up for three events.

477
00:23:03,340 --> 00:23:04,610
However, in that case,

478
00:23:04,690 --> 00:23:06,920
I might have no time for homework.

479
00:23:07,110 --> 00:23:08,530
What a pity.

480
00:23:08,620 --> 00:23:09,530
Mao Ying Jian,

481
00:23:09,620 --> 00:23:11,010
make sure he has no regrets.

482
00:23:11,100 --> 00:23:11,530
He's got privilege,

483
00:23:11,610 --> 00:23:12,850
and he can't sign up for any event.

484
00:23:12,930 --> 00:23:13,490
No!

485
00:23:13,580 --> 00:23:15,000
Sir, I want to participate.

486
00:23:17,420 --> 00:23:18,490
Don't be a dull boy.

487
00:23:18,580 --> 00:23:19,490
You're in the best condition of your life,

488
00:23:19,580 --> 00:23:21,120
do some exercise.

489
00:23:24,340 --> 00:23:25,880
Which one do you want to sign up for?

490
00:23:35,260 --> 00:23:36,840
I don't want to join any sports.

491
00:23:37,060 --> 00:23:37,960
Why?

492
00:23:38,120 --> 00:23:39,400
I'm not interested in it,

493
00:23:39,570 --> 00:23:40,840
and have no time for it.

494
00:23:44,290 --> 00:23:44,850
Sit down,

495
00:23:44,940 --> 00:23:46,030
talk to me.

496
00:23:52,210 --> 00:23:53,360
Wu Zhi Xun,

497
00:23:53,780 --> 00:23:55,240
you've been excellent

498
00:23:55,380 --> 00:23:56,560
with your study.

499
00:23:57,460 --> 00:23:58,440
You made me

500
00:23:58,810 --> 00:24:01,160
a very proud headteacher.

501
00:24:01,620 --> 00:24:02,120
However,

502
00:24:02,210 --> 00:24:04,280
I'm proud as a teacher.

503
00:24:04,650 --> 00:24:06,270
But if I were your friend,

504
00:24:06,380 --> 00:24:07,680
or your brother,

505
00:24:08,050 --> 00:24:09,360
I would like to ask you

506
00:24:09,780 --> 00:24:10,760
to think about it

507
00:24:11,020 --> 00:24:12,210
with such precious youth,

508
00:24:12,300 --> 00:24:14,960
don't you think you're a little too dull?

509
00:24:16,530 --> 00:24:17,600
I've heard that

510
00:24:17,850 --> 00:24:21,200
your father is a post-graduate
from a well-known college.

511
00:24:22,540 --> 00:24:24,350
He's only one step from
becoming a professor.

512
00:24:26,420 --> 00:24:27,840
Unlike your father.

513
00:24:28,850 --> 00:24:31,000
My father's a technician.

514
00:24:31,370 --> 00:24:32,560
He needs to rush around.

515
00:24:32,690 --> 00:24:34,360
The equipment in the northeast region

516
00:24:34,450 --> 00:24:36,310
all depends on my father.

517
00:24:36,540 --> 00:24:38,070
Therefore, we move a lot,

518
00:24:38,850 --> 00:24:40,730
changing from one place to another.

519
00:24:40,820 --> 00:24:43,030
My mum and I, we move with him.

520
00:24:43,810 --> 00:24:45,640
So I haven't had many
friends since I was a kid.

521
00:24:46,380 --> 00:24:48,200
Therefore, I'm very envious

522
00:24:48,500 --> 00:24:50,800
of those who have childhood friends.

523
00:24:51,850 --> 00:24:53,730
The first year on my job,

524
00:24:53,820 --> 00:24:54,250
one of my colleagues

525
00:24:54,340 --> 00:24:55,090
from the same office

526
00:24:55,180 --> 00:24:55,970
got married.

527
00:24:56,060 --> 00:24:57,320
I went to his wedding.

528
00:24:58,110 --> 00:24:59,280
And his childhood friends,

529
00:24:59,450 --> 00:24:59,970
schoolmates

530
00:25:00,060 --> 00:25:01,240
crowded three whole tables.

531
00:25:01,530 --> 00:25:02,720
After the wedding,

532
00:25:03,780 --> 00:25:04,790
all those friends,

533
00:25:04,880 --> 00:25:06,210
they drank

534
00:25:06,300 --> 00:25:08,000
and talked about their
memories of childhood

535
00:25:08,780 --> 00:25:10,370
from afternoon to midnight.

536
00:25:10,450 --> 00:25:12,360
And I sat beside them,

537
00:25:12,970 --> 00:25:13,450
and listened

538
00:25:13,530 --> 00:25:15,050
about all those small things.

539
00:25:15,140 --> 00:25:17,200
They kept talking and talking.

540
00:25:20,450 --> 00:25:22,310
And I really

541
00:25:23,580 --> 00:25:25,040
wanted to cry.

542
00:25:27,460 --> 00:25:28,490
Back in our school days,

543
00:25:28,580 --> 00:25:30,230
nobody knew

544
00:25:31,540 --> 00:25:32,990
how to cherish those memories.

545
00:25:33,860 --> 00:25:35,400
When you've grown up,

546
00:25:35,580 --> 00:25:36,600
you will come to
understand the importance.

547
00:25:37,380 --> 00:25:38,510
But it's already too late.

548
00:25:38,980 --> 00:25:40,840
The people and the
time have passed you by.

549
00:25:42,180 --> 00:25:44,280
The reason I choose to become a teacher

550
00:25:45,020 --> 00:25:46,480
is I believe that

551
00:25:47,500 --> 00:25:48,370
the best place

552
00:25:48,460 --> 00:25:49,690
in this world

553
00:25:49,780 --> 00:25:51,080
is the campus.

554
00:25:51,980 --> 00:25:53,360
You've studied so hard.

555
00:25:53,450 --> 00:25:54,450
So tell me,

556
00:25:54,540 --> 00:25:56,430
what are you studying for?

557
00:25:57,140 --> 00:25:58,750
To get into the best college.

558
00:26:01,420 --> 00:26:03,560
That's what I thought
when I was a student.

559
00:26:04,500 --> 00:26:06,110
But as a teacher,

560
00:26:06,880 --> 00:26:07,990
I think

561
00:26:08,650 --> 00:26:10,290
studying is to know better,

562
00:26:10,380 --> 00:26:11,630
and understand the world.

563
00:26:12,290 --> 00:26:14,680
Getting into college is
only a short-term goal.

564
00:26:15,120 --> 00:26:16,470
It's not your entire life.

565
00:26:20,020 --> 00:26:21,190
Go to your class.

566
00:26:21,820 --> 00:26:24,120
Next time, you'll tell me your story.

567
00:26:24,810 --> 00:26:25,880
Now go to class.

568
00:26:45,500 --> 00:26:47,270
Fan Shui Shui, you'll be throwing discus.

569
00:26:47,880 --> 00:26:48,630
Why?

570
00:26:48,710 --> 00:26:49,590
No.

571
00:26:49,790 --> 00:26:51,990
With your weight, discus
throw is the best choice.

572
00:26:52,080 --> 00:26:53,440
I'll throw you out like a discus.

573
00:26:53,530 --> 00:26:54,410
Alright, alright.

574
00:26:54,500 --> 00:26:55,690
Just help me with it.

575
00:26:55,780 --> 00:26:57,440
Nobody wants to do it.

576
00:26:57,880 --> 00:26:58,760
Ba Dan.

577
00:26:58,880 --> 00:26:59,370
Will you

578
00:26:59,460 --> 00:27:01,000
do the high jump?

579
00:27:03,100 --> 00:27:04,090
Him?

580
00:27:04,180 --> 00:27:05,400
He's so short.

581
00:27:07,940 --> 00:27:08,570
Trust me.

582
00:27:08,660 --> 00:27:09,540
Sign me up.

583
00:27:09,700 --> 00:27:11,090
No problem.

584
00:27:11,180 --> 00:27:12,910
Alright, I'll sign you up.

585
00:27:13,450 --> 00:27:14,720
You know nothing.

586
00:27:15,740 --> 00:27:16,720
What about you?

587
00:27:17,340 --> 00:27:19,440
Whatever.

588
00:27:20,050 --> 00:27:20,850
Does this mean, you are all-round,

589
00:27:20,930 --> 00:27:22,290
or you are no-round?

590
00:27:22,370 --> 00:27:23,960
All-round of course.

591
00:27:24,260 --> 00:27:25,140
And you?

592
00:27:25,380 --> 00:27:27,550
400-meter relay.

593
00:27:27,650 --> 00:27:28,970
I think I'm good at running.

594
00:27:29,060 --> 00:27:30,630
Last time at the station.

595
00:27:30,850 --> 00:27:32,690
I was dragging you along.

596
00:27:32,780 --> 00:27:34,230
It was because I ran fast.

597
00:27:34,420 --> 00:27:35,350
What?

598
00:27:35,620 --> 00:27:36,670
Did you two hold hands?

599
00:27:36,860 --> 00:27:38,040
When?

600
00:27:38,380 --> 00:27:40,040
None of your business.

601
00:27:42,540 --> 00:27:43,420
Mao,

602
00:27:43,700 --> 00:27:45,570
sign Li Jin Bu up for the 400-meter relay.

603
00:27:45,660 --> 00:27:46,540
Ok.

604
00:27:46,820 --> 00:27:47,870
Xiao,

605
00:27:48,300 --> 00:27:49,430
will you do the hurdle race?

606
00:27:49,770 --> 00:27:50,690
It's pretty hard.

607
00:27:50,780 --> 00:27:51,880
Join with me, will you?

608
00:27:53,490 --> 00:27:54,130
Ok.

609
00:27:54,220 --> 00:27:55,400
Alright.

610
00:27:57,250 --> 00:27:58,130
Qing Tong,

611
00:27:58,820 --> 00:28:00,040
How about you?

612
00:28:00,620 --> 00:28:01,610
Is there anything

613
00:28:01,700 --> 00:28:03,290
that requires stillness,

614
00:28:03,380 --> 00:28:04,290
like holding ping-pong
for the longest time.

615
00:28:04,380 --> 00:28:06,440
Why don't you just go knitting sweaters?

616
00:28:07,100 --> 00:28:08,610
What else can I sign up for?

617
00:28:08,690 --> 00:28:10,320
What's left?

618
00:28:10,700 --> 00:28:11,690
Only 5000-meter left.

619
00:28:11,770 --> 00:28:12,720
Just go with it.

620
00:28:12,860 --> 00:28:13,790
You don't need to run fast,

621
00:28:13,870 --> 00:28:14,530
just finish the whole race.

622
00:28:14,620 --> 00:28:16,120
There's no skill required.

623
00:28:16,580 --> 00:28:17,930
No skills required for 5000-metre?

624
00:28:18,020 --> 00:28:19,610
You might run until you die.

625
00:28:19,690 --> 00:28:20,570
Don't do it.

626
00:28:22,010 --> 00:28:24,280
If I can't last till the end,

627
00:28:24,410 --> 00:28:25,470
can I slope off in the middle of it?

628
00:28:25,560 --> 00:28:26,850
As long as you're not embarrassed,

629
00:28:26,940 --> 00:28:28,640
you can slope off any time.

630
00:28:29,220 --> 00:28:30,030
Ok, I'll do it.

631
00:28:30,120 --> 00:28:31,440
Alright, I'll sign you up.

632
00:28:36,060 --> 00:28:37,880
5000-meters sound good to me,

633
00:28:38,380 --> 00:28:39,710
how about we do it together?

634
00:28:40,580 --> 00:28:41,570
We can't finish the race anyway,

635
00:28:41,660 --> 00:28:43,110
let's just slope off.

636
00:28:43,980 --> 00:28:44,690
We can run slowly

637
00:28:44,770 --> 00:28:46,000
at the end of the line.

638
00:28:46,090 --> 00:28:47,310
I need to go out.

639
00:29:08,300 --> 00:29:09,600
Wu Zhi Xun.

640
00:29:11,580 --> 00:29:12,800
What now?

641
00:29:18,140 --> 00:29:19,920
You don't look well.

642
00:29:21,020 --> 00:29:22,930
You mean I need more exercise

643
00:29:23,020 --> 00:29:24,370
and need to play some sports,

644
00:29:24,460 --> 00:29:26,270
so I should sign
up for the sports meeting?

645
00:29:27,500 --> 00:29:29,110
You're even worse than Wu.

646
00:29:29,540 --> 00:29:31,080
You call him Wu too?

647
00:29:31,380 --> 00:29:32,130
What's the problem?

648
00:29:32,210 --> 00:29:33,510
Nothing.

649
00:29:33,730 --> 00:29:35,200
So what did he say?

650
00:29:36,810 --> 00:29:37,960
He told me to make friends,

651
00:29:38,100 --> 00:29:39,440
and don't waste my youth.

652
00:29:46,580 --> 00:29:47,970
It's not like that

653
00:29:48,050 --> 00:29:49,090
I want you to exercise

654
00:29:49,180 --> 00:29:50,360
or make friends.

655
00:29:50,450 --> 00:29:51,730
So why?

656
00:29:51,820 --> 00:29:53,920
I just want you to be happy.

657
00:29:55,090 --> 00:29:56,210
You're always alone.

658
00:29:56,290 --> 00:29:57,970
You must be very lonely.

659
00:29:58,050 --> 00:29:59,730
Everyone's going to the sports meeting,

660
00:29:59,810 --> 00:30:01,670
and here you are alone in the classroom.

661
00:30:02,180 --> 00:30:03,050
I hate for you to

662
00:30:03,140 --> 00:30:04,670
always be alone.

663
00:30:07,660 --> 00:30:08,830
Just sign up for one event.

664
00:30:10,420 --> 00:30:11,600
So you can go out to the playground,

665
00:30:11,690 --> 00:30:12,410
get some sunshine,

666
00:30:12,500 --> 00:30:14,720
listen to the radio and meet with others.

667
00:30:16,740 --> 00:30:17,950
Just one.

668
00:30:18,180 --> 00:30:19,010
How about this,

669
00:30:19,100 --> 00:30:20,120
take a bet with me.

670
00:30:20,420 --> 00:30:20,970
The loser

671
00:30:21,050 --> 00:30:22,250
treats the winner to barbecue.

672
00:30:22,340 --> 00:30:23,220
Ok?

673
00:30:23,900 --> 00:30:24,490
Well,

674
00:30:24,570 --> 00:30:25,960
can you win the first prize?

675
00:30:27,210 --> 00:30:28,360
The first prize...

676
00:30:28,740 --> 00:30:29,620
Or the top three,

677
00:30:30,100 --> 00:30:31,560
that also count.

678
00:30:31,830 --> 00:30:32,710
Alright.

679
00:30:33,490 --> 00:30:34,810
Deal!

680
00:30:34,900 --> 00:30:36,010
There's another group event,

681
00:30:36,100 --> 00:30:37,610
tug-of war, we need a few more people.

682
00:30:37,700 --> 00:30:38,530
Anyone?

683
00:30:38,620 --> 00:30:39,510
Please raise your hands.

684
00:30:39,620 --> 00:30:40,500
Him.

685
00:30:46,500 --> 00:30:49,550
We'll do some personal training today.

686
00:30:49,890 --> 00:30:50,870
Sir,

687
00:30:51,180 --> 00:30:52,510
I can't train today.

688
00:30:52,820 --> 00:30:54,920
Anyone else? Step out of the line.

689
00:30:56,660 --> 00:30:57,370
You two

690
00:30:57,460 --> 00:30:58,760
help me record the names.

691
00:31:04,020 --> 00:31:05,440
Why can't they train?

692
00:31:05,860 --> 00:31:07,010
It's their bad days.

693
00:31:07,100 --> 00:31:08,030
Bad days?

694
00:31:14,580 --> 00:31:15,600
What does bad days mean?

695
00:31:16,100 --> 00:31:16,970
Could you please

696
00:31:17,050 --> 00:31:19,560
stop asking around about other girls?

697
00:31:21,220 --> 00:31:23,750
You've been very awful to me lately.

698
00:31:24,020 --> 00:31:26,230
Is your mind on someone else?

699
00:31:26,310 --> 00:31:27,190
Go to hell.

700
00:31:28,460 --> 00:31:30,210
I just took a bet with Wu Zhi Xun.

701
00:31:30,300 --> 00:31:32,010
If I can make it into the top three,

702
00:31:32,100 --> 00:31:33,790
he'll treat me to a barbecue.

703
00:31:34,260 --> 00:31:36,400
Didn't he stop helping you study?

704
00:31:36,530 --> 00:31:38,650
How come you get closer?

705
00:31:38,730 --> 00:31:40,720
We're friends now.

706
00:31:40,810 --> 00:31:43,280
I'm the one that talked
him into joining the game.

707
00:31:43,540 --> 00:31:45,040
See? I'm very important.

708
00:31:45,420 --> 00:31:46,720
No, I don't see it.

709
00:31:47,340 --> 00:31:49,040
Anyone else can't train today?

710
00:31:49,260 --> 00:31:49,890
Sir.

711
00:31:49,980 --> 00:31:51,090
I'm having my bad days,

712
00:31:51,170 --> 00:31:52,440
can I skip the training today?

713
00:31:54,890 --> 00:31:56,550
You want to be punished?

714
00:32:00,260 --> 00:32:02,120
Why can't I have bad days?

715
00:32:12,660 --> 00:32:14,560
Leehom Wang just released a new album.

716
00:32:15,140 --> 00:32:17,320
I'm crazy about him lately.

717
00:32:18,820 --> 00:32:20,310
Who's your favourite star?

718
00:32:20,700 --> 00:32:21,600
None.

719
00:32:24,860 --> 00:32:26,400
Alright, we'll skip it.

720
00:32:27,740 --> 00:32:29,960
You remember our bet?

721
00:32:31,460 --> 00:32:32,510
What bet?

722
00:32:33,940 --> 00:32:36,470
You'll buy me barbecue if
I make into the top three.

723
00:32:37,250 --> 00:32:38,280
Oh.

724
00:32:40,540 --> 00:32:41,870
I didn't know you forgot.

725
00:32:42,140 --> 00:32:44,120
That's alright, I'll remind you.

726
00:32:44,530 --> 00:32:46,040
Did you memorize all the notes?

727
00:32:48,170 --> 00:32:49,400
I'm working on it.

728
00:32:57,980 --> 00:32:59,880
This is for Fan Shui Shui.

729
00:33:11,100 --> 00:33:12,280
I'm leaving, Xiao.

730
00:33:12,570 --> 00:33:13,640
Bye.

731
00:33:18,520 --> 00:33:19,210
Tong,

732
00:33:19,290 --> 00:33:20,760
are you going or not?

733
00:33:21,140 --> 00:33:22,810
Shush, I'm trying to
memorize the notebook.

734
00:33:22,900 --> 00:33:25,440
Li Qing Tong is just
bewitched by somebody.

735
00:33:25,860 --> 00:33:27,640
She can't see anything but the notebook.

736
00:33:27,820 --> 00:33:28,990
Doesn't even go home.

737
00:33:35,620 --> 00:33:36,530
Oh my God.

738
00:33:36,620 --> 00:33:38,640
This is appalling.

739
00:33:39,180 --> 00:33:40,060
Let me have a look.

740
00:33:44,610 --> 00:33:45,490
Oh my god.

741
00:33:45,930 --> 00:33:46,850
He's so strong,

742
00:33:46,940 --> 00:33:48,350
this book is dog-eared and falling out.

743
00:33:48,620 --> 00:33:50,170
That's because he had gone
through it a hundred times.

744
00:33:50,260 --> 00:33:51,980
Right?

745
00:33:52,070 --> 00:33:53,450
How about your books?

746
00:33:53,540 --> 00:33:54,640
All look brand new.

747
00:33:54,820 --> 00:33:56,030
You guys stay away.

748
00:33:56,120 --> 00:33:57,590
I can't focus.

749
00:34:02,700 --> 00:34:03,920
Come, let's go home.

750
00:34:04,940 --> 00:34:05,730
Bye.

751
00:34:05,820 --> 00:34:07,270
We're leaving.

752
00:34:21,739 --> 00:34:22,620
Excuse me.

753
00:34:22,860 --> 00:34:23,650
May I know

754
00:34:23,739 --> 00:34:25,310
if those books have arrived yet?

755
00:34:27,340 --> 00:34:28,710
Yes, hang on.

756
00:34:32,840 --> 00:34:35,060
[Leehom Wang]

757
00:34:51,989 --> 00:34:56,270
[Leehom Wang]

758
00:34:56,400 --> 00:34:59,900
[Tieyuan No. 3 Middle School]

759
00:34:59,900 --> 00:35:01,080
Don't you think you look like coach Anzai?

760
00:35:01,170 --> 00:35:01,810
You look like coach Anzai.

761
00:35:01,900 --> 00:35:03,090
You really do.

762
00:35:03,170 --> 00:35:04,410
You look like Anzai's girlfriend.

763
00:35:04,490 --> 00:35:05,910
Fan Shui Shui you admitted it.

764
00:35:12,500 --> 00:35:14,050
Your dress is so pretty.

765
00:35:14,140 --> 00:35:15,730
It's the latest design by Ameilian.

766
00:35:15,810 --> 00:35:16,880
It's so pretty.

767
00:35:17,060 --> 00:35:17,890
It must be very expensive?

768
00:35:17,980 --> 00:35:18,990
Not really.

769
00:35:19,130 --> 00:35:21,170
This colour looks great on you.

770
00:35:21,260 --> 00:35:23,190
It's not on the market yet.

771
00:35:23,530 --> 00:35:24,450
I know Ameilian.

772
00:35:24,540 --> 00:35:25,420
Shut up.

773
00:35:27,300 --> 00:35:28,880
Let's go shopping sometime.

774
00:35:29,220 --> 00:35:29,850
So pretty.

775
00:35:29,940 --> 00:35:30,950
I want one too.

776
00:35:31,040 --> 00:35:32,170
I hear that Ameilian has
introduced many new designs lately.

777
00:35:32,260 --> 00:35:34,190
It really looks so great on you.

778
00:35:36,290 --> 00:35:39,000
It's the latest design of Ameilian.

779
00:35:39,690 --> 00:35:40,770
It must be very expensive.

780
00:35:40,860 --> 00:35:42,480
It's ok.

781
00:35:42,650 --> 00:35:43,750
Boring.

782
00:35:44,060 --> 00:35:45,690
Well, she wears an Ameilian.

783
00:35:45,780 --> 00:35:47,210
What's Ameilian?

784
00:35:47,290 --> 00:35:48,090
Ameilian

785
00:35:48,170 --> 00:35:50,040
is the brand only for

786
00:35:50,130 --> 00:35:51,330
those pretentious girls.

787
00:35:51,420 --> 00:35:52,240
It's very expensive.

788
00:35:52,330 --> 00:35:53,120
It's supposedly

789
00:35:53,210 --> 00:35:55,890
an exclusive brand for the hottest girls.

790
00:35:55,970 --> 00:35:57,170
It sounds

791
00:35:57,260 --> 00:35:58,560
so superficial.

792
00:35:59,100 --> 00:36:00,640
Well, you can't afford it anyway.

793
00:36:02,620 --> 00:36:04,160
Who said I can't?

794
00:36:04,380 --> 00:36:05,490
Li Qing Tong,

795
00:36:05,580 --> 00:36:06,490
you're such a baby,

796
00:36:06,580 --> 00:36:08,630
talking behind others' backs.

797
00:36:09,580 --> 00:36:11,410
I can say it again right in front of you.

798
00:36:11,490 --> 00:36:12,250
It's just superficial,

799
00:36:12,340 --> 00:36:13,480
and ugly, and pretentious.

800
00:36:13,570 --> 00:36:15,200
We both know who's
the ugly one between us.

801
00:36:15,300 --> 00:36:16,920
What's the point of being jealous?

802
00:36:20,000 --> 00:36:21,010
You!

803
00:36:21,100 --> 00:36:21,890
Don't be such a baby, Li Qing Tong.

804
00:36:21,980 --> 00:36:23,150
Let it go.

805
00:36:24,250 --> 00:36:26,430
She splashed all over me.

806
00:36:33,700 --> 00:36:35,330
Multitask.

807
00:36:35,420 --> 00:36:37,000
Respect.

808
00:36:37,540 --> 00:36:39,750
Not yet.

809
00:36:40,430 --> 00:36:41,170
I still have

810
00:36:41,260 --> 00:36:42,680
two pages left.

811
00:36:42,780 --> 00:36:43,960
What's this?

812
00:36:44,050 --> 00:36:45,080
Let me have a look.

813
00:36:46,000 --> 00:36:46,880
No.

814
00:36:46,980 --> 00:36:48,090
No one else can look
at Wu Zhi Xun's notebook.

815
00:36:48,180 --> 00:36:49,770
Didn't we all flip through it?

816
00:36:49,860 --> 00:36:50,490
That's not the same.

817
00:36:50,580 --> 00:36:52,510
Reading carefully equals leaking out.

818
00:36:52,600 --> 00:36:53,500
No.

819
00:36:54,580 --> 00:36:56,260
Not even me?

820
00:37:01,560 --> 00:37:03,200
[Tieyuan No. 3 Middle School]

821
00:37:03,200 --> 00:37:05,670
[Year 1 Class 3, Year 2 Class 3,
Year 2 Class 2]

822
00:37:07,860 --> 00:37:09,130
The area for tug-of-war

823
00:37:09,220 --> 00:37:10,800
is right behind the goal area.

824
00:37:10,890 --> 00:37:12,310
Attention please.

825
00:37:13,260 --> 00:37:14,090
Turn up the voice.

826
00:37:14,180 --> 00:37:16,330
The hurdles are on
the lane in front of us.

827
00:37:16,410 --> 00:37:17,880
We should all take notes.

828
00:37:21,370 --> 00:37:22,090
Hello.

829
00:37:22,180 --> 00:37:22,890
Hello.

830
00:37:22,890 --> 00:37:23,130
[Year 1 Class 3, Year 3 Class 1]

831
00:37:23,130 --> 00:37:24,120
Students.

832
00:37:24,210 --> 00:37:25,920
Teachers.

833
00:37:26,260 --> 00:37:27,140
Alright.

834
00:37:27,220 --> 00:37:31,000
[Tieyuan No. 3 Middle School
Summer Sports Meeting]

835
00:37:39,220 --> 00:37:40,840
Tying a bowknot for a sports meeting.

836
00:37:40,930 --> 00:37:42,150
How is she supposed to play sports?

837
00:37:48,140 --> 00:37:48,810
You go first.

838
00:37:48,900 --> 00:37:50,800
I need to go bring something.

839
00:38:03,610 --> 00:38:04,960
What are you doing here?

840
00:38:05,540 --> 00:38:06,720
What event did you sign up for?

841
00:38:07,660 --> 00:38:08,890
None of your business.

842
00:38:08,980 --> 00:38:10,430
Come on, tell me.

843
00:38:11,210 --> 00:38:12,090
5000-meter race.

844
00:38:12,180 --> 00:38:13,360
Scared?

845
00:38:13,660 --> 00:38:14,700
5000-meter race?

846
00:38:15,100 --> 00:38:16,810
Aren't you afraid you might run
until you die?

847
00:38:18,620 --> 00:38:20,840
Who talks like that?

848
00:38:22,780 --> 00:38:23,660
Here.

849
00:38:28,900 --> 00:38:30,040
Since it's free, I may as well drink it.

850
00:38:32,420 --> 00:38:33,780
The chocolate you got looks good.

851
00:38:33,860 --> 00:38:34,800
Can I have it?

852
00:38:36,020 --> 00:38:38,270
Hell no.

853
00:38:38,700 --> 00:38:41,280
This is for the number
one student in our grade.

854
00:38:42,330 --> 00:38:43,450
That four-eyed guy?

855
00:38:43,540 --> 00:38:44,440
Don't be so rude!

856
00:38:44,530 --> 00:38:45,210
He's got a name,

857
00:38:45,300 --> 00:38:46,290
Wu Zhi Xun.

858
00:38:46,380 --> 00:38:47,650
People like him are the worst.

859
00:38:47,730 --> 00:38:49,230
Think of themselves as something special.

860
00:38:49,320 --> 00:38:50,760
He is something special.

861
00:38:51,900 --> 00:38:52,530
People like you,

862
00:38:52,620 --> 00:38:54,200
won't understand.

863
00:38:55,580 --> 00:38:56,730
Get off.

864
00:38:56,820 --> 00:38:58,360
Ask that four-eyed to buy you one.

865
00:39:02,180 --> 00:39:03,520
Cheapskate.

866
00:39:05,210 --> 00:39:06,880
Distinguished teachers,

867
00:39:06,970 --> 00:39:08,770
dear students.

868
00:39:08,850 --> 00:39:11,560
Good morning.

869
00:39:14,900 --> 00:39:15,910
Today,

870
00:39:16,060 --> 00:39:19,290
we, members of Tieyuan
No. 3 Middle School,

871
00:39:19,380 --> 00:39:21,450
gather here with great joy

872
00:39:21,540 --> 00:39:24,600
to welcome the
summer sports meeting.

873
00:39:24,690 --> 00:39:26,580
This sports meeting

874
00:39:26,670 --> 00:39:29,370
is not only a sport event,

875
00:39:29,460 --> 00:39:30,970
but also a great opportunity

876
00:39:31,060 --> 00:39:32,690
for teachers and students

877
00:39:32,780 --> 00:39:35,190
to demonstrate their
abilities and passion.

878
00:39:35,270 --> 00:39:36,030
Today,

879
00:39:36,120 --> 00:39:38,680
we compete on the track.

880
00:39:38,770 --> 00:39:39,530
In the future,

881
00:39:39,620 --> 00:39:42,990
we'll make our mark in the world arena.

882
00:39:43,070 --> 00:39:43,960
Today,

883
00:39:44,050 --> 00:39:46,850
we compete on the track.

884
00:39:46,930 --> 00:39:47,910
In the future,

885
00:39:48,000 --> 00:39:51,410
we'll brave the waves of the real world.

886
00:39:51,500 --> 00:39:53,310
It's like we are attending
the Olympic Games.

887
00:39:53,580 --> 00:39:55,070
Who's talking?

888
00:39:55,260 --> 00:39:56,480
Quiet!

889
00:40:10,340 --> 00:40:11,770
I want all of you to uphold the spirit of

890
00:40:11,860 --> 00:40:13,490
"friendship comes first,"

891
00:40:13,580 --> 00:40:16,090
"competition comes second."

892
00:40:16,180 --> 00:40:17,810
Show your ability.

893
00:40:17,900 --> 00:40:19,690
Show your virtues.

894
00:40:19,780 --> 00:40:23,900
I wish you all a great performance

895
00:40:23,990 --> 00:40:26,890
and a successful sports meeting.

896
00:40:26,970 --> 00:40:28,630
Now,

897
00:40:28,720 --> 00:40:30,490
I declare

898
00:40:30,580 --> 00:40:35,960
the summer sports meeting of
No.3 Middle School of Tieyuan begins.

899
00:40:46,330 --> 00:40:48,040
Here, you need your strength.

900
00:40:50,900 --> 00:40:52,000
Thanks.

901
00:40:55,780 --> 00:40:56,990
Stop eating.

902
00:40:57,380 --> 00:40:58,390
Are you here to picnic?

903
00:40:58,480 --> 00:40:59,650
You are here to attend the sports meeting.

904
00:40:59,740 --> 00:41:01,170
Stop eating.

905
00:41:01,260 --> 00:41:02,250
Those who take part in
tug-of-war gather here.

906
00:41:02,340 --> 00:41:03,050
Come here.

907
00:41:03,140 --> 00:41:03,910
Cheer them up.

908
00:41:04,000 --> 00:41:06,470
Come on! Come on!

909
00:41:06,560 --> 00:41:07,570
Move it! Move it!

910
00:41:07,660 --> 00:41:08,600
Come on! Come on!

911
00:41:09,990 --> 00:41:14,250
Come on! Come on!

912
00:41:14,340 --> 00:41:15,360
Watch me.

913
00:41:16,780 --> 00:41:17,710
Stop eating you guys.

914
00:41:17,800 --> 00:41:18,780
Come on.

915
00:41:26,340 --> 00:41:27,610
Tug-of-war has always been

916
00:41:27,700 --> 00:41:29,250
the last event at other schools.

917
00:41:29,340 --> 00:41:31,520
Why do we have to do it
at the beginning?

918
00:41:31,860 --> 00:41:34,310
Huang Si Hai knows
nothing about sports.

919
00:41:34,900 --> 00:41:36,770
He used to be professional soccer player.

920
00:41:36,850 --> 00:41:37,690
What do you know?

921
00:41:37,780 --> 00:41:39,320
Just stop complaining.

922
00:41:39,660 --> 00:41:40,790
Professional?

923
00:41:41,540 --> 00:41:43,040
Which class do we compete with?

924
00:41:43,140 --> 00:41:45,560
Class 1 of senior.

925
00:41:46,140 --> 00:41:46,450
Thanks.

926
00:41:46,530 --> 00:41:46,730
Ok.

927
00:41:46,820 --> 00:41:48,390
Warm up first.

928
00:41:48,900 --> 00:41:50,640
Here, attention please.

929
00:41:51,000 --> 00:41:52,880
We've got a rough start.

930
00:41:53,130 --> 00:41:55,520
Our opponent was the champion last time.

931
00:41:55,700 --> 00:41:56,960
But relax,

932
00:41:57,060 --> 00:41:58,310
we are as good as them.

933
00:41:58,400 --> 00:41:59,050
Come on,

934
00:41:59,140 --> 00:42:00,200
teach them a lesson.

935
00:42:00,700 --> 00:42:03,440
It's the first event, let's get excited!

936
00:42:04,220 --> 00:42:05,090
Are we going to win?

937
00:42:05,180 --> 00:42:05,900
Yes.

938
00:42:05,990 --> 00:42:06,750
Loudly!

939
00:42:06,840 --> 00:42:08,170
Yes!

940
00:42:08,260 --> 00:42:09,090
My foot.

941
00:42:09,180 --> 00:42:09,690
Let's go.

942
00:42:09,780 --> 00:42:11,440
Stop that.

943
00:42:12,050 --> 00:42:13,380
It hurts!

944
00:42:13,470 --> 00:42:15,880
Let's hear Zhi Xun's plan.

945
00:42:16,770 --> 00:42:18,170
We're generally taller than them

946
00:42:18,260 --> 00:42:19,360
but thinner.

947
00:42:19,460 --> 00:42:20,910
Therefore, we need to line up

948
00:42:21,000 --> 00:42:21,730
from the tallest to the shortest,

949
00:42:21,820 --> 00:42:23,030
from the thinnest to the heaviest.

950
00:42:23,420 --> 00:42:24,850
Duan Xiao and I will stand in the front,

951
00:42:24,930 --> 00:42:26,380
girls can stand in the middle

952
00:42:26,460 --> 00:42:27,920
and the rest of the boys should
stand at the end of the line,

953
00:42:28,140 --> 00:42:29,610
taking good use of your weights

954
00:42:29,700 --> 00:42:31,280
to hold the whole line.

955
00:42:31,850 --> 00:42:33,910
Most of them use the
slogan "one, two, three".

956
00:42:34,000 --> 00:42:35,830
So we should only count to two.

957
00:42:36,180 --> 00:42:36,690
At one, we hold.

958
00:42:36,780 --> 00:42:37,480
At two, we pull.

959
00:42:37,570 --> 00:42:39,160
The louder the slogan, the better.

960
00:42:39,450 --> 00:42:41,280
We need to break up their rhythm.

961
00:42:41,380 --> 00:42:43,160
It's the only way for us to win.

962
00:42:43,620 --> 00:42:44,450
Simple and clear.

963
00:42:44,540 --> 00:42:45,640
Everyone understand?

964
00:42:46,300 --> 00:42:46,690
Yes.

965
00:42:46,780 --> 00:42:48,150
Here, cheer yourselves up.

966
00:42:48,880 --> 00:42:49,360
One.

967
00:42:49,450 --> 00:42:49,770
Two.

968
00:42:49,860 --> 00:42:50,330
Three.

969
00:42:50,420 --> 00:42:51,210
Fighting.

970
00:42:51,300 --> 00:42:52,180
Go, go, go.

971
00:42:55,580 --> 00:42:56,390
Everyone,

972
00:42:56,480 --> 00:42:57,880
two out of three.

973
00:42:58,420 --> 00:42:59,890
Friendship first and competition second.

974
00:42:59,980 --> 00:43:00,770
Remember.

975
00:43:00,860 --> 00:43:01,290
If there's no problem,

976
00:43:01,380 --> 00:43:03,280
let the game begin.

977
00:43:04,180 --> 00:43:05,090
Dude,

978
00:43:05,180 --> 00:43:06,630
don't cry if you lose.

979
00:43:06,780 --> 00:43:08,150
It's not settled yet.

980
00:43:09,260 --> 00:43:10,270
You got some backbones.

981
00:43:12,940 --> 00:43:13,240
Come on.

982
00:43:13,330 --> 00:43:14,450
Line up.

983
00:43:14,540 --> 00:43:15,090
Line up.

984
00:43:15,180 --> 00:43:16,400
Relax, dude.

985
00:43:16,650 --> 00:43:17,720
Beat them up.

986
00:43:18,260 --> 00:43:19,150
Of course.

987
00:43:21,240 --> 00:43:22,120
Piece of cake.

988
00:43:22,660 --> 00:43:23,770
Remember our plan?

989
00:43:23,860 --> 00:43:24,570
Remember.

990
00:43:24,660 --> 00:43:25,540
Ready.

991
00:43:25,650 --> 00:43:26,490
Get ready,

992
00:43:26,580 --> 00:43:27,460
pay attention to the whistle.

993
00:43:34,640 --> 00:43:35,620
Come on.

994
00:43:35,790 --> 00:43:39,290
One two. One two.

995
00:43:39,380 --> 00:43:45,910
Come on! Come on!

996
00:43:46,000 --> 00:43:48,050
One two. One two.

997
00:43:48,140 --> 00:43:50,710
Come on! Come on!

998
00:43:50,800 --> 00:43:51,570
One two.

999
00:43:51,660 --> 00:43:59,360
Come on! Come on!

1000
00:44:08,620 --> 00:44:09,720
Referee.

1001
00:44:10,330 --> 00:44:11,130
Referee.

1002
00:44:11,210 --> 00:44:12,530
Come on! Come on!

1003
00:44:12,620 --> 00:44:14,760
Referee, they broke the rules.

1004
00:44:16,050 --> 00:44:18,740
Come on! Come on!

1005
00:44:19,420 --> 00:44:20,760
Which one of you breach the rule?

1006
00:44:22,770 --> 00:44:23,780
They got extra people.

1007
00:44:23,860 --> 00:44:25,070
That's a lie. We didn't.

1008
00:44:25,160 --> 00:44:26,700
I saw it! Them!

1009
00:44:40,440 --> 00:44:41,320
Stop it!

1010
00:44:43,600 --> 00:44:44,290
Stop!

1011
00:44:44,380 --> 00:44:45,130
Stop.

1012
00:44:45,210 --> 00:44:46,030
Stop.

1013
00:44:46,120 --> 00:44:47,000
Stop fighting.

1014
00:44:47,260 --> 00:44:48,140
Stop it.

1015
00:44:49,540 --> 00:44:50,330
Stop.

1016
00:44:50,420 --> 00:44:51,300
Stop.

1017
00:44:51,880 --> 00:44:52,760
Stop.
